  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle and peel lengths off your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> with a peeler until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Combine your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> in a heatproof bowl and stir until the sugar has dissolved</p><p>Add your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>quick-pickled courgette</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1669726004042-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1669726004042-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1669726004042-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1669726004042-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1669726004042-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> (save them for later) and chop the<strong> softer inner core[s]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669726010757-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669726010757-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669726010757-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669726010757-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669726010757-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> cold water and <strong>tough</strong> <strong>outer lemongrass layers</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1669726015393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1669726015393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1669726015393-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1669726015393-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1669726015393-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 3/4 of the <strong>sliced onion </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) and cook for 3-4 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1669726020680-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1669726020680-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1669726020680-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1669726020680-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1669726020680-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lean pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to the onion and increase the heat to high</p><p>Cook for 5-7 min or until beginning to crisp, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once crisp, add your<strong> fish sauce</strong> and <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until everything is brown, sticky and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Watch it like a hawk to prevent the sauce from burning!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1669726026327-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1669726026327-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1669726026327-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1669726026327-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1669726026327-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Carefully chop your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1669726031361-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1669726031361-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1669726031361-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1669726031361-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1669726031361-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped peanuts</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Remove the <strong>lemongrass outer layers</strong> from the rice and discard, then fluff the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong> with a fork and stir your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> through – this is your <strong>black sesame rice</strong></p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped mint</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> through the pork – this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style sticky lemongrass lean pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1669726035288-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1669726035288-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1669726035288-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1669726035288-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1669726035288-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced onion </strong>to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>carrot salad</strong></p><p>Drain the<strong> quick-pickled courgette</strong>, discard the liquid</p><p>Serve the <strong>Vietnamese-style sticky lemongrass lean pork</strong> with the <strong>black sesame rice</strong>, <strong>quick-pickled courgette</strong> and <strong>carrot salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
